age, Cornwall, England":"Breage, Cornwall, England","Cornouailles, Angleterre":"Cornwall, England"},"nl":{"–13 November 1392":"–13 november 1392","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1362–Male":"1362–Overleden","1373–Male":"1373–Overleden","–1392":"–1392","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1365–Female":"1365–Overleden","1320–Male":"1320–Overleden","1338–1361":"1338–1361","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1290":"1290","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","13 November 1392":"13 november 1392","1410":"1410","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","22 September 1392":"22 september 1392","19 janvier 1361":"19 januari 1361","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Great Waltham, Essex, , England":"Great Waltham, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Godolphin Manor, Helston, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Holcombe Burnell, Devon, England":"Holcombe Burnell, Devon, England","Breage, Cornwall, England":"Breage, Cornwall, England","Cornouailles, Angleterre":"Cornwall, England"},"en":{"–13 November 1392":"–13 November 1392","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1362–Male":"1362–Deceased","1373–Male":"1373–Deceased","–1392":"–1392","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1365–Female":"1365–Deceased","1320–Male":"1320–Deceased","1338–1361":"1338–1361","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1290":"1290","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","13 November 1392":"13 November 1392","1410":"1410","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","22 September 1392":"22 September 1392","19 janvier 1361":"19 January 1361","1328":"1328","1317":"1317","Great Waltham, Essex, , England":"Great Waltham, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Godolphin Manor, Helston, Cornwall, England, United Kingdom":"Helston, Cornwall, England","Holcombe Burnell, Devon, England":"Holcombe Burnell, Devon, England","Breage, Cornwall, England":"Breage, Cornwall, England","Cornouailles, Angleterre":"Cornwall, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Godolphin","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["Cornish, English: locative name from Godolphin (Cornwall), recorded as  <i>Wulgholgan</i> in 1194."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":17,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705191,"age":42,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705192,"age":55,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":64,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":109,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Margaret Godolphin was born in Breage, Cornwall, England as the daughter of David Godolphin esquire and Melina Cowling. She had at least 1 daughter with Robert Dennis. She died on 13 November 1392, in Helston, Cornwall, England."},"et":{"–13 November 1392":"–13. november 1392","1361–1410":"1361–1410","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1373–Male":"1373–Surnud","–1392":"–1392","1325–1392":"1325–1392","1365–Female":"1365–Surnud","1320–Male":"1320–Surnud","1338–1361":"1338–1361","1373":"1373","1362":"1362","1361":"1361","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1290":"1290","1338":"1338","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1325":"1325","13 November 1392":"13. november 1392","1410":"1410","1365":"1365",